 With the festive season in full swing and holiday plans finalised it is worthwhile to consider how best to include your beloved pets in your holiday schedule. Image: sourced Image: sourced Added to the above it is advisable to make sure your pets all have some form of identification. A microchip is an ideal way to ensure your pet can be identified when you’re not around, but an ID tag attached to a sturdy, comfortable collar would also be a good way to ensure you can be contacted in the event that your pet is lost or manages to leave your property. According to the SPCA, “Whether you are planning to spend the holidays at home, or elsewhere it is essential that you ensure that your pets are supervised and safe. All their needs must be catered for at all times to ensure their safety and happiness.”